The paper deals with the connectivity problem in Cognitive Radio Networks (CRNs) through spectrum assignments. This problem is related to network connectivity and graph theory, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-categories of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Information Theory (cs.IT), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
